# tpd/

The Technical Product Design (TPD) for Intent v2.4.0 provides comprehensive technical specification covering system architecture, requirements, design decisions, implementation strategy, deployment guidance, and technical challenges. The TPD is organized as a numbered series of markdown documents with a central index file for navigation and includes a preamble for Claude explaining the document's purpose and key concepts.

## Files

- `technical_product_design.md` -- Main index and entry point for the TPD; contains preamble to Claude and links to all sections with plugin architecture overview
- `1_introduction.md` -- Purpose, scope, definitions, system overview, and references for Intent v2.4.0 rebrand from STP
- `2_requirements.md` -- Functional and non-functional requirements for documentation, LLM collaboration, backlog integration, configuration, and process support
- `3_architecture.md` -- System architecture overview with documentation structure, command-line interface design, and process guidelines
- `4_detailed_design.md` -- Directory structure, JSON configuration system, document templates, and component implementation details (AS-BUILT)
- `5_implementation_strategy.md` -- Development approach, steel thread breakdown, and phased task organization for building Intent
- `6_deployment_and_operations.md` -- Installation methods (global bootstrap, manual, project-specific), initialization procedures, and system requirements (AS-BUILT)
- `7_technical_challenges_and_mitigations.md` -- LLM context window management, shell portability, documentation maintenance, and adoption barriers (AS-BUILT)
- `8_appendices.md` -- Glossary, command reference, configuration schema, and command usage examples (AS-BUILT)
